Class ClusterManagementServiceBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.geode.management.internal.api.BaseManagementServiceBuilder<ClusterManagementServiceBuilder>
      • org.apache.geode.management.client.ClusterManagementServiceBuilder

  • @Experimental
public class ClusterManagementServiceBuilder
extends org.apache.geode.management.internal.api.BaseManagementServiceBuilder<ClusterManagementServiceBuilder>
    This builder facilitates creating a ClusterManagementService using either (or both) a ConnectionConfig or a ClusterManagementServiceTransport. For typical usage it should be sufficient to only use a ClusterManagementServiceConnectionConfig. For example: 
     ClusterManagementService service = new ClusterManagementServiceBuilder()
     .setPort(7070)
     .setHost("localhost")
     .build();

    If no transport is set a public transport of RestTemplateClusterManagementServiceTransport will be used and configured with the provided config.
